# Eval metric targets — DESIGN.md's Evaluation table, made executable.
#
# Uncomment a metric to activate it. `make eval-heuristic` prints PASS/FAIL per
# activated metric; `make eval-gate` additionally exits non-zero on any FAIL
# (wire that into CI once the golden set is real). Keys are either
# HeuristicReport fields in the eval runner (pipelines/run.py) or the name of
# a custom grader registered in graders/custom/ (your project's own primary
# metric — see that package's docstring). Every backend present in the project
# is held to the same targets.
#
# Shipped fully commented out: a fresh project's golden set is example data —
# set real targets when DESIGN.md's Evaluation section is filled in.

